<br />
Conditions (3)<br />
 Small Hope x2<br />
 Under Foot    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The general appeal of the Free Peoples side comes from starting all the main female characters of the movies, and hoping that your opponent will be dazzled by just how pretty they are (this actually happened once).<br />
As you all probably know, LR is now x-listed, so this will my last week for this deck at tourneys.<br />
<br />
Generally, have elves use the bows (brilliant, eh?) and have Eowyn discard the javelin to up the archery total, which Arwen, Legolas and Eowyn play off of.<br />
If you win the bid for first, use Stables to get Winfold, and then use Border Patrol (if you&#39;re behind and have been playing your site, or get lucky and your opponent plays a plains site) to add exertions on minions.<br />
Play Blades Drawn when you lose confidence in Arwen and Eowyn&#39;s ability to beatdown and/or wound minions.<br />
Later in the game, if Arwen and Eowyn are exhausted/dead, or you&#39;re against those Uruks that don&#39;t take archery wounds, you can use Cirdan to take down the bigger minions.<br />
Galadriel is there to look good and keep your opponent&#39;s support area from getting too crowded. She usually dies in a sacrificial manner to some massive minion later in the game.<br />
<br />
The shadow side adds burdens with Small Hope, Guards and Lieutenants. This deck has a good chance of corrupting one of the alternate ringbearers, if you play those cards at the right time.<br />
With a high resistance ringbearer, you generally go for a swarm/beatdown.<br />
<br />
Yeah, first posted deck. Hope I did this right.<br />
Remember my decktech newbness is your reviews. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
